{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019WrKv2ixRbHNcj5s6h7Qn8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GxjAVsL6web4mgxUrZRqiq","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"PLAN='# Spark-Pi Namespace — Maintenance Upgrade Plan\nDate: 2026-06-23\nPrepared by: Platform Engineering (read-only audit)\nNamespace: spark-pi\n\n---\n\n## Current State Summary\n\n| Resource | Key Facts |\n|---|---|\n| spark-master Deployment | apache/spark:3.5.3, 1 replica, cpu 200m-500m, mem 512Mi-1Gi, securityContext: {} |\n| spark-worker Deployment | apache/spark:3.5.3, 1 replica, SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1, securityContext: {} |\n| spark-pi Job | local[2] mode, 1000 Pi iterations, driver-memory=512m, backoffLimit=0, completed successfully |\n| spark-pi Role | Grants pods/services/configmaps/PVCs CRUD — pods permission was added post-initial-apply (drift) |\n| spark-pi-role-binding | Correctly binds spark-pi-role to spark-pi SA |\n| ServiceAccount default | No automountServiceAccountToken: false |\n| Service spark-master | ClusterIP, ports 7077 (spark) + 8080 (webui) |\n| NetworkPolicy | None |\n| LimitRange / ResourceQuota | None |\n\nPre-existing compliance audit is recorded in ConfigMap config-audit (findings.txt).\n\n---\n\n## Change Plan\n\nChanges are ordered by risk tier (Critical → High → Medium → Low) within\neach tier ordered to minimise blast radius. Each step includes a rollback note.\n\n---\n\n### STEP 1 — [CRITICAL] SEC-1: Add security contexts to all workloads\n\n**Problem:** All three workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker\nDeployment, spark-pi Job) have securityContext: {} at both pod and container\nlevel. Containers are presumed to run as root.\n\n**Change:** Patch each workload manifest to add a pod-level and\ncontainer-level securityContext. Minimum required controls:\n\n  Pod-level:\n    securityContext:\n      runAsNonRoot: true\n      runAsUser: 185          # Spark upstream non-root UID in apache/spark images\n      runAsGroup: 185\n      fsGroup: 185\n\n  Container-level (all three containers):\n    securityContext:\n      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n      readOnlyRootFilesystem: false   # Spark writes logs/tmp — keep false unless log dir is a volume\n      capabilities:\n        drop: [\"ALL\"]\n\n**Target resources:**\n  - deploy/spark-master  (container: spark-master)\n  - deploy/spark-worker  (container: spark-worker)\n  - job/spark-pi         (container: spark-submit) — recreate job with new spec\n\n**Order:**\n  1a. Apply to spark-worker Deployment first (least traffic impact).\n  1b. Apply to spark-master Deployment (rolling restart, 1 replica — brief outage).\n  1c. Recreate spark-pi Job with updated spec (old completed job can be deleted\n      after confirming the new one passes).\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.securityContext}{'\\n'}{end}\"\n  # Confirm runAsNonRoot=true and capabilities.drop=[ALL] on each running pod.\n  kubectl logs -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master | head -20\n  # Confirm master starts without permission errors.\n  kubectl logs -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker | head -20\n  # Confirm worker connects to master (look for \"Successfully registered with master\").\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master && kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-worker\n\n---\n\n### STEP 2 — [HIGH] RBAC-4: Remove stale pod permission from spark-pi-role\n\n**Problem:** The live spark-pi-role grants CRUD on \"pods\". The\nlast-applied-configuration annotation proves pods was NOT in the original\nRole declaration — it was added manually after creation. In local[2] mode\nthe SparkPi driver spawns no executor pods, so this permission is unused\nand represents undeclared privilege expansion.\n\n**Change:** Edit spark-pi-role to remove \"pods\" from the resources list.\nFinal resources list: [\"services\", \"configmaps\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"].\n\n  kubectl edit role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi\n  # Remove \"- pods\" from the resources array, then save.\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl get role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{.rules[*].resources}\"\n  # Output must NOT contain \"pods\".\n  kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n  # Expected: \"no\"\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl patch role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi --type=json \\\n  -p '\"'\"'[{\"op\":\"add\",\"path\":\"/rules/0/resources/-\",\"value\":\"pods\"}]'\"'\"'\n\n---\n\n### STEP 3 — [HIGH] NET-1: Add NetworkPolicy to restrict traffic\n\n**Problem:** Zero NetworkPolicy objects exist. Spark master WebUI (8080)\nand protocol port (7077) accept connections from any pod in the cluster.\n\n**Change:** Create two NetworkPolicy resources:\n\n  Policy 1 — spark-master ingress:\n    Allow ingress on 7077 only from pods with label app=spark-worker\n    Allow ingress on 8080 only from operator/monitoring namespaces (label team=platform)\n    Deny all other ingress to spark-master pods.\n\n  Policy 2 — spark-worker egress to master:\n    Allow egress from spark-worker pods to spark-master pods on port 7077.\n    Allow egress for DNS (port 53 UDP/TCP to kube-dns).\n    Deny all other egress from worker pods.\n\n  Policy 3 — default-deny baseline:\n    A catch-all default-deny-ingress policy for the namespace so new pods\n    are isolated until an explicit allow policy is added.\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl get networkpolicy -n spark-pi\n  # Confirm three policies are present.\n  kubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- nc -zv spark-master 7077\n  # Expected: connection succeeds (worker→master on 7077 is allowed).\n  kubectl run nettest --image=busybox --restart=Never -n default -- \\\n    nc -zv spark-master.spark-pi.svc.cluster.local 7077 2>&1 || true\n  # Expected: connection refused/timed out (external pods blocked).\n  kubectl delete pod nettest -n default\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl delete networkpolicy -n spark-pi --all\n  (restores open networking; apply only if services are unreachable)\n\n---\n\n### STEP 4 — [MEDIUM] QUOTA-1: Add LimitRange and ResourceQuota\n\n**Problem:** No LimitRange or ResourceQuota exists. Future workloads (or\nmanifest edits) could omit resource limits and run unconstrained.\n\n**Change:**\n\n  LimitRange (default + max per container):\n    type: Container\n    default:       cpu=200m, memory=512Mi\n    defaultRequest: cpu=100m, memory=256Mi\n    max:           cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\n\n  ResourceQuota (namespace ceiling):\n    hard:\n      requests.cpu: \"1\"\n      requests.memory: 2Gi\n      limits.cpu: \"2\"\n      limits.memory: 4Gi\n      count/pods: \"10\"\n\n  Note: Current workloads (spark-master + spark-worker + spark-pi pod) total\n  requests.cpu=600m, requests.memory=1.5Gi — comfortably within the quota.\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl describe limitrange -n spark-pi\n  kubectl describe resourcequota -n spark-pi\n  # Confirm Used < Hard for all resource types.\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl delete limitrange --all -n spark-pi && kubectl delete resourcequota --all -n spark-pi\n\n---\n\n### STEP 5 — [MEDIUM] IMAGE-3: Pin container images to immutable digest\n\n**Problem:** All containers use the mutable tag apache/spark:3.5.3.\nA malicious or accidental registry push could silently change what\nthis tag resolves to.\n\n**Change:**\n  1. Resolve the current digest:\n       docker pull apache/spark:3.5.3\n       docker inspect apache/spark:3.5.3 --format \"{{.RepoDigests}}\"\n       # Or: crane digest apache/spark:3.5.3\n\n  2. Replace image references in all three manifests:\n       FROM: apache/spark:3.5.3\n       TO:   apache/spark:3.5.3@sha256:<verified-digest>\n\n  Apply to:\n    - deploy/spark-master\n    - deploy/spark-worker\n    - future re-creations of job/spark-pi (Jobs are immutable once created)\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl get deploy spark-master -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}\"\n  # Must contain @sha256:\n  kubectl get deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}\"\n  # Must contain @sha256:\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl set image deploy/spark-master spark-master=apache/spark:3.5.3 -n spark-pi\n             kubectl set image deploy/spark-worker spark-worker=apache/spark:3.5.3 -n spark-pi\n\n---\n\n### STEP 6 — [LOW] RBAC-5: Disable token automount on the default ServiceAccount\n\n**Problem:** The default ServiceAccount in spark-pi does not set\nautomountServiceAccountToken: false. Any pod that omits serviceAccountName\nreceives an API token for the default SA.\n\n**Change:**\n  kubectl patch serviceaccount default -n spark-pi \\\n    -p '\"'\"'{\"automountServiceAccountToken\": false}'\"'\"'\n\n**Verify:**\n  kubectl get serviceaccount default -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{.automountServiceAccountToken}\"\n  # Expected: false\n\n**Rollback:** kubectl patch serviceaccount default -n spark-pi \\\n    -p '\"'\"'{\"automountServiceAccountToken\": null}'\"'\"'\n\n---\n\n## Execution Order Summary\n\n| Step | ID | Severity | Change | Requires Downtime |\n|------|-----|----------|--------|-------------------|\n| 1 | SEC-1 | Critical | Add security contexts | Rolling restart (brief) |\n| 2 | RBAC-4 | High | Remove pods from role | No |\n| 3 | NET-1 | High | Add NetworkPolicy | No (additive) |\n| 4 | QUOTA-1 | Medium | Add LimitRange + Quota | No (additive) |\n| 5 | IMAGE-3 | Medium | Pin image digest | Rolling restart (brief) |\n| 6 | RBAC-5 | Low | Disable default SA automount | No |\n\nSteps 2, 3, 4, 6 are non-disruptive and can be applied in a single\nmaintenance window without a Spark outage.\nSteps 1 and 5 each require a rolling restart of the Deployments.\nRecommended sequencing: apply steps 2/3/4/6 first, then steps 1+5\ntogether in the same rolling restart to minimise restart cycles.\n\n---\n\n## Pre-Change Checklist\n\n- [ ] Obtain approval from team lead and operations manager\n- [ ] Schedule change window (recommend off-peak hours)\n- [ ] Snapshot current manifests: kubectl get deploy,job,role,rolebinding,sa,svc -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-pi-backup-$(date +%Y%m%d).yaml\n- [ ] Confirm cluster has capacity for rolling restarts (>1 schedulable node for HA)\n- [ ] Notify downstream consumers of spark-master:8080 (WebUI) of potential brief outage\n\n## Post-Change Verification\n\n- [ ] All pods in spark-pi Running with correct securityContext\n- [ ] spark-pi-role does NOT include pods resource\n- [ ] NetworkPolicy objects present and traffic from external pods blocked\n- [ ] ResourceQuota and LimitRange present; used < hard limits\n- [ ] Image references include @sha256: digest\n- [ ] default SA has automountServiceAccountToken: false\n- [ ] Run a new spark-pi Job and confirm it completes successfully\n- [ ] Check spark-worker logs for successful master registration\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Existing audit: kubectl get configmap config-audit -n spark-pi -o jsonpath=\"{.data.findings\\.txt}\"\n- Spark on Kubernetes security guide: https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/running-on-kubernetes.html\n- CIS Kubernetes Benchmark v1.8 (sections 5.2 Pod Security, 5.3 Network Policies, 5.4 Secrets)\n- apache/spark image: https://hub.docker.com/r/apache/spark\n'\n\nkubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=\"plan.md=${PLAN}\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2316,"cache_read_input_tokens":33796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2316},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b256bcd2-55cd-49cd-8262-d0cab05d5831","uuid":"b6729724-6905-48fa-80f2-8107b16ea2e7","request_id":"req_011CcLupY5fy7fQstD23pa4Y"}
